assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: KUWAZAWA Holdings Corporation operates as a construction materials trading company in Japan. It offers basic materials, such as cement, ready-mixed concretes; civil engineering materials; steel products; interior and exterior materials; kitchens and unit baths; and water supply and drainage equipment. The company also provides lumber for housing and pre-cut materials, as well as offers interior materials and housing equipment. In addition, the company provides designs public facilities, hospitals, hotels, condominiums, and detached properties, as well as offers transportation for construction materials, crane leasing, civil engineering work, and warehousing, as well as offers transportation for construction materials, crane leasing, civil engineering work, and warehousing. Further, it develops logistics services. Additionally, the company offers sheet metal roofs and heavy items, such as construction and civil engineering equipment. It also provides cement silos for materials used for ground improvement. In addition, the company offers windows, doors, glass, and products related to houses, condominiums, commercial facilities, and buildings, as well as provides cleaning, facility management, security, and building maintenance services; and insurance agency business. KUWAZAWA Holdings Corporation was founded in 1933 and is headquartered in Sapporo, Japan.
